Docco is a quick-and-dirty, hundred-line-long, literate-programming-style
documentation generator. For more information, see:

http://jashkenas.github.com/docco/

---

Sample bash script to traverse a hierarchy of js src and flatten it into a docs folder in the app root.

  # Run from project root
  function fd {
    app_root="Sites/xx"
    js_root="$app_root/xx"
    cd ~/$js_root
    docco *.js
    list="xx xx xx xx"
    for dir in $list;
    do 
      find $dir -name "*.js" -print0 | xargs -0 docco
    done
    mv ~/$js_root/docs/*.html ~/$app_root/docs/
    rm -r -f ~/$js_root/docs
  }
